descriptor.description: An irradiance unit which is equal to one microeinstein per square meter per second or 10^[-6] microeinstein/sm^[2].

descriptor.label: radiance unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the power of electromagnetic radiation through space or through a material medium in the form of electromagnetic waves.

descriptor.descriptorElement: watt per steradian per square meter
descriptor.descriptor: watt per steradian per square meter
descriptor.label: watt per steradian per square meter
descriptor.description: A radiance unit which is equal to one watt of radiant power incident per steradian solid angle per one square meter projected area of the source, as viewed from the given direction.

descriptor.label: acceleration unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the rate of change of velocity in either speed or direction.

descriptor.label: meter per second per second
descriptor.description: An acceleration unit which is equal to the acceleration an object changing its velocity by 1meter/s over a time period that equals one second.

descriptor.label: density unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.

descriptor.label: area density unit
descriptor.description: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a given area.

descriptor.label: kilogram per square meter
descriptor.description: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in meters squared.

descriptor.label: mass density unit
descriptor.description: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.

descriptor.label: linear density unit
descriptor.description: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.

descriptor.label: kilogram per meter
descriptor.description: An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by one meter.

descriptor.label: electric potential difference
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.

descriptor.label: millivolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousandth of a volt or 10^[-3] V.

descriptor.label: microvolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one millionth of a volt or 10^[-6] V.

descriptor.label: megavolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one million volts or 10^[6] V.

descriptor.label: volt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to the work per unit charge. One volt is the potential difference required to move one coulomb of charge between two points in a circuit while using one joule of energy.

descriptor.label: kilovolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousand volts or 10^[3] V.

descriptor.label: nanovolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one billionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.

descriptor.label: picovolt
descriptor.description: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one trillionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.

descriptor.label: electric charge
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the quantity of unbalanced electricity in a body (either positive or negative) and construed as an excess or deficiency of electrons.

descriptor.label: coulomb
descriptor.description: An electrical charge unit which is equal to the amount of charge transferred by a current of 1 ampere in 1 second.

descriptor.label: magnetic flux unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of quantity of magnetism, taking account of the strength and the extent of a magnetic field.

descriptor.label: volt-hour
descriptor.description: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to 3600 Wb.

descriptor.label: kilovolt-hour
descriptor.description: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to one thousand volt-hours.

descriptor.label: weber
descriptor.description: A magnetic flux unit which is equal to the amount of flux that when linked with a single turn of wire for an interval of one second will induce an electromotive force of one volt.

descriptor.label: magnetic flux density unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the strength of a magnetic field.

descriptor.label: tesla
descriptor.description: A magnetic flux density unit which is equal to one weber per square meter.

descriptor.label: surface tension unit
descriptor.description: A unit which is a standard measure of the ability of a liguid to attraction of molecules at its surface as a result of unbalanced molecular cohesive forces.

descriptor.label: dyne per cm
descriptor.description: A surface tension unit which is equal to one dyne per centimeter.

descriptor.label: newton per meter
descriptor.description: A surface tension unit which is equal to one newton per meter.

descriptor.label: viscosity unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the internal resistance of fluids to flow.

descriptor.label: poise
descriptor.description: A viscosity unit which is equal to one dyne second per square centimeter.

descriptor.label: hour
descriptor.description: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

descriptor.label: year
descriptor.description: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which is science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

descriptor.label: area unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the amount of a 2-dimensional flat surface.

descriptor.label: square meter
descriptor.description: An area unit which is equal to an area enclosed by a square with sides each 1 meter long.

descriptor.label: square centimeter
descriptor.description: An area unit which is equal to one thousand of square meter or 10^[-3] m^[2].

descriptor.label: square millimeter
descriptor.description: An area unit which is equal to one millionth of a square meter or 10^[-6] m^[2].

descriptor.label: angular velocity unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the rate of angular movement about an axis; the angle rotated in a given time.

descriptor.label: radian per second
descriptor.description: An angular unit velocity which is equal to about 9.54930 rpm (revolutions per minute).

descriptor.label: dimensionless unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units.

descriptor.label: ratio unit
descriptor.description: A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another.

descriptor.label: fraction
descriptor.description: A dimensionless ratio unit which relates the part (the numerator) to the whole (the denominator).

descriptor.label: mole fraction
descriptor.description: A concentration unit which denotes the number of moles of solute as a proportion of the total number of moles in a solution.

descriptor.label: decibel
descriptor.description: An ratio unit which is an indicator of sound power per unit area.

descriptor.label: percent
descriptor.description: A dimensionless ratio unit which denotes numbers as fractions of 100.

descriptor.label: purity percentage
descriptor.description: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the homogeneity of a biomaterial.

descriptor.label: mass volume percentage
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of the substance in a mixture as a percentage of the volume of the entire mixture.

descriptor.label: confluence percentage
descriptor.description: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the density of an attached or monolayer culture (e.g., cell culture).

descriptor.label: mass percentage
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

descriptor.label: parts per notation
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which describes the amount of one substance in another. It is the ratio of the amount of the substance of interest to the amount of that substance plus the amount of the substance.

descriptor.label: parts per quadrillion
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[15].

descriptor.label: parts per hundred
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 100 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same.

descriptor.label: parts per thousand
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1000 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same.

descriptor.label: parts per million
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[6].

descriptor.label: parts per billion
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[9].

descriptor.label: parts per trillion
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the amount of a given substance in a total amount of 1,000,000,000 regardless of the units of measure used as long as they are the same or 1 part in 10^[12].

descriptor.label: count unit
descriptor.description: A dimensionless unit which denotes a simple count of things.

descriptor.label: colony forming unit
descriptor.description: A dimensionless count unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers.

descriptor.label: molecule count
descriptor.description: A dimensionless count unit which denotes the number of molecules.

descriptor.label: plaque forming unit
descriptor.description: A dimensionless count unit which a measure of plague forming units in a given volume.

descriptor.label: base pair
descriptor.description: A count unit which contains one nucleotide.

descriptor.label: pH
descriptor.description: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

descriptor.label: absorbance unit
descriptor.description: A dimensionless logarithmic unit assigned to a measure of absorbance of light through a partially absorbing substance, defined as -log10(I/I_0) where I = transmitted light and I_0 = incident light.

descriptor.label: information unit
descriptor.description: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of information.

descriptor.label: byte
descriptor.description: An information unit which is equal to 8 bits.

descriptor.label: kibibyte
descriptor.description: An information unit which is equal to 1024 B.

descriptor.label: mebibyte
descriptor.description: An information unit which is equal to 1024 KiB.

descriptor.label: bit
descriptor.description: An information unit which refers to a digit in the binary numeral system, which consists of base 2 digits (ie there are only 2 possible values

descriptor.label: kilobyte
descriptor.description: An information unit which is equal to 1000 bytes.

descriptor.label: megabyte
descriptor.description: An information unit which is equal to 1000 kB.

descriptor.label: image resolution unit
descriptor.description: An information unit which is a standard measure of the detail an image holds.

descriptor.label: chroma sampling unit
descriptor.description: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of spatial detail in an image.

descriptor.label: dynamic range unit
descriptor.description: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of contrast available in a pixel.

descriptor.label: spatial resolution unit
descriptor.description: An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the way luminance and chrominance may be sampled at different levels.

descriptor.label: micron pixel
descriptor.description: A spatial resolution unit which is equal to a pixel size of one micrometer.

descriptor.label: dots per inch
descriptor.description: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the printing resolution, in particular the number of individual dots of ink a printer or toner can produce within a linear one-inch space.

descriptor.label: pixels per inch
descriptor.description: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the resolution of a computer display, related to the size of the display in inches and the total number of pixels in the horizontal and vertical directions.

descriptor.label: pixels per millimeter
descriptor.description: A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the number of pixels in one millimeter length or width of a digital image divided by the physical length or width of a printed image.

descriptor.label: volumetric flow rate unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which is a standard measure of the volume of fluid which passes through a given surface per unit time .

descriptor.label: microliters per minute
descriptor.description: A volumetric flow rate unit which is equal to one microliter volume through a given surface in one minute.

descriptor.label: unit of molarity
descriptor.description: A derived concentration unit which is a standard measure of the number of moles of a given substance per liter of solution.

descriptor.label: millimolar
descriptor.description: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of a molar or 10^[-3] M.

descriptor.label: picomolar
descriptor.description: A unit of molarity which is equal to 10^[-12] M.

descriptor.label: micromolar
descriptor.description: A unit of molarity which is equal to one millionth of a molar or 10^[-6] M.

descriptor.label: molar

descriptor.label: nanomolar
descriptor.description: A unit of molarity which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a molar or 10^[-9] M.

descriptor.label: femtomolar
descriptor.description: A unit of molarity which is equal to 10^[-15] M.

descriptor.label: unit of molality
descriptor.description: A derived concentration unit which is a standard measure of the number of moles of a given substance per kilogram of solvent.

descriptor.label: millimolal
descriptor.description: A molality unit which is equal to one thousandth of a molal or 10^[-3] m.

descriptor.label: picomolal
descriptor.description: A molality unit which is equal to 10^[-12] m.

descriptor.label: unit per liter

descriptor.label: mass per unit volume
descriptor.description: A concentration unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume (density).

descriptor.label: gram per liter

descriptor.label: microgram per liter

descriptor.label: gram per cubic centimeter

descriptor.label: pascal second

descriptor.label: conduction unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium.

descriptor.label: electrical conduction unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor).

descriptor.label: siemens
descriptor.description: An electrical conduction unit which is equal to A/V.

descriptor.label: heat conduction unit
descriptor.description: A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the spontaneous transfer of thermal energy through matter, from a region of higher temperature to a region of lower temperature.

descriptor.label: watt per meter kelvin
descriptor.description: An heat conduction unit which is equal to one watt divided by meter kelvin.

descriptor.label: electric field strength unit
descriptor.description: The electric field strength is a derived unit which is a measure of the potential difference between two points some distance apart.

descriptor.label: volt per meter
descriptor.description: The volt per meter is a unit of electric field strength equal to the a potential difference of 1 volt existing between two points that are 1 meter apart.

An information unit which is equal to 1000 kB.
An information unit which is a standard measure of the detail an image holds.
An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of spatial detail in an image.
An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the amount of contrast available in a pixel.
An image resolution unit which is a standard measure of the way luminance and chrominance may be sampled at different levels.
A spatial resolution unit which is equal to a pixel size of one micrometer.
A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the printing resolution, in particular the number of individual dots of ink a printer or toner can produce within a linear one-inch space.

A spatial resolution unit which is a standard measure of the resolution of a computer display, related to the size of the display in inches and the total number of pixels in the horizontal and vertical directions.
A pressure unit which is equal to the pressure or stress on a surface caused by a force of 1 newton spread over a surface of 1 m^[2].
A unit of pressure equal to the amount of fluid pressure one millimeter deep in mercury at zero degrees centigrade on Earth.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the amount of the action of a catalyst.
A catalytic unit activity which is equal to the activity of a catalyst in moles per second, such as the amount of an enzyme needed to transform one mole of substrate per second.
A catalytic unit activity which is equal to the amount of the enzyme that catalyzes the conversion of 1 micro mole of substrate per minute.
A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of temperature in a particular temperature scale.
A temperature derived unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.
A temperature derived unit which is equal to one Kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The Centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

A derived unit which is a standard measure of the amount of radiation emitted by a given radiation source as well as the amount of radiation absorbed or deposited in a specific material by a radiation source.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the transformation (disintegration) rate of a radioactive substance.
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to one thousandth of a curie or 10^[-3] Ci.
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the number of light emissions produced by ionizing radiation in one minute.
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per second or there is one atom disintegration per second (dps).
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which there are 3.7 x 10^[10] atom disintegration per second (dps).
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to one millionth of a curie or 10^[-6] Ci.
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per minute or there is one atom disintegration per minute.
An activity (of a radionuclide) unit which is equal to the activity of a quantity of radioactive material in which one nucleus decays per second or there is one atom disintegration per second.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the energy imparted by ionizing radiation to unit mass of matter such as tissue.
An absorbed dose unit which is equal to 0.01 gray (Gy).
An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one millionth of a gray or 10^[-6] Gy.
An absorbed dose unit which is equal to the absorption of one joule of radiation energy by one kilogram of matter.
An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one thousandth of a gray or 10^[-3] Gy.
An absorbed dose unit which is equal to one thousandth of a millionth of a gray or 10^[-9] Gy.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the expression of dose in terms of its biological effect.
A dose equivalent unit which is equal to the absorption of one joule of radiation energy by one kilogram of matter.
A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one thousandth of a millionth of a sievert or 10^[-9] Sv.
A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one thousandth of a sievert or 10^[-3] Sv.
A dose equivalent unit which is equal to one millionth of a sievert or 10^[-6] Sv.
A dose equivalent unit which when multiplied by hundred is equal to one sievert or 1 Sv. 1 Sv is equal to 100 rem.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the quantity that expresses the ability of radiation to ionize air and thereby create electric charges which can be collected and measured.

An exposure unit which is equal to the amount of radiation required to liberate positive and negative charges of one electrostatic unit of charge in 1 cm^[3] of air at standard temperature and pressure (STP). This corresponds to the generation of approximately 2.0810^[9] ion pairs.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the estimate of the stochastic effect that a non-uniform radiation dose has on a human.
from the Broad - Patrick AID min Assay Sheet
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the intensity of light.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the luminous flux incident on a unit area.
An illuminance unit which is equal to the illuminance produced by 1 lumen evenly spread over an area 1 m^[2].
An illuminance unit which is equal to the illuminance produced by 1 lumen evenly spread over an area 1 foot^[2]. One footcandle is equal to 10.76 lux.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the flow of radiant energy.
A luminous flux unit which is equal to the luminous flux emitted into 1 steradian by a point source of 1 candela.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the intensity of electromagnetic radiation.
A radiant intensity unit which is equal to one kilogram meter squared per second cubed per steradian.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the luminous intensity impinging on a given area.
A luminance unit which is equal to a luminous intensity of one candela radiating from a surface whose area is one square meter.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the power of electromagnetic radiation at a surface, per unit area.
An irradiance unit which is equal to 1 watt of radiant power incident per one square meter surface area.

unit.unitElement: microeinstein per square meter per second
unit.description: An irradiance unit which is equal to one microeinstein per square meter per second or 10^[-6] microeinstein/sm^[2].
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the power of electromagnetic radiation through space or through a material medium in the form of electromagnetic waves.

unit.unitElement: watt per steradian per square meter
unit.description: A radiance unit which is equal to one watt of radiant power incident per steradian solid angle per one square meter projected area of the source, as viewed from the given direction.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the rate of change of velocity in either speed or direction.
An acceleration unit which is equal to the acceleration an object changing its velocity by 1meter/s over a time period that equals one second.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.
A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a given area.
An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by the surface area in meters squared.
A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.
A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass exerting an influence on a one-dimensional object.
An area density unit which is equal to the mass of an object in kilograms divided by one meter.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousandth of a volt or 10^[-3] V.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one millionth of a volt or 10^[-6] V.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one million volts or 10^[6] V.

An electric potential difference unit which is equal to the work per unit charge. One volt is the potential difference required to move one coulomb of charge between two points in a circuit while using one joule of energy.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousand volts or 10^[3] V.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one billionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.
An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one trillionth of a volt or 10^[-12] V.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the quantity of unbalanced electricity in a body (either positive or negative) and construed as an excess or deficiency of electrons.
An electrical charge unit which is equal to the amount of charge transferred by a current of 1 ampere in 1 second.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of quantity of magnetism, taking account of the strength and the extent of a magnetic field.
A magnetic flux unit which is equal to 3600 Wb.
A magnetic flux unit which is equal to one thousand volt-hours.
A magnetic flux unit which is equal to the amount of flux that when linked with a single turn of wire for an interval of one second will induce an electromotive force of one volt.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the strength of a magnetic field.
A magnetic flux density unit which is equal to one weber per square meter.
A unit which is a standard measure of the ability of a liguid to attraction of molecules at its surface as a result of unbalanced molecular cohesive forces.
A surface tension unit which is equal to one dyne per centimeter.
A surface tension unit which is equal to one newton per meter.
A derived unit which is a standard measure of the internal resistance of fluids to flow.
A viscosity unit which is equal to one dyne second per square centimeter.
A viscosity unit which is equal to one pascale per second.
A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium.
A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor).
An electrical conduction unit which is equal to A/V.
A derived unit which represents a standard measurement of the spontaneous transfer of thermal energy through matter, from a region of higher temperature to a region of lower temperature.
An heat conduction unit which is equal to one watt divided by meter kelvin.
The electric field strength is a derived unit which is a measure of the potential difference between two points some distance apart.
The volt per meter is a unit of electric field strength equal to the a potential difference of 1 volt existing between two points that are 1 meter apart.
